            "answer_text": "It is currently the year of our Lord 2018, and today\u2019s date is Monday, June 25th, using the Gregorian calendar. Anno Domini, year of the Lord, is normally abbreviated AD. It counts the years after the (estimated, and probably about three years off) birth of our Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ. The year of His birth is counted as year 1. The years before the birth of Jesus are marked as BC, Before Christ. ",
